parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The violent shaking of the front end can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes violently
the vehicle pulls to one side
the front end hops or bounces
and the driver may experience a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wanders
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the driver may experience a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension system can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle bounces or hops excessively
the front end shakes or vibrates
and the driver may experience a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination of the fuel tank can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to costly repairs and replacement of fuel injectors, fuel pumps, and other components.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the vehicle sputters or runs rough
the fuel filter becomes clogged
and the fuel tank lining chips off and enters the fuel system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of fuel injectors can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to costly repairs and replacement of fuel injectors, fuel pumps, and other components.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the vehicle sputters or runs rough
and the fuel injectors become clogged or fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to costly repairs and replacement of fuel pumps, fuel injectors, and other components.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the vehicle sputters or runs rough
and the fuel pump fails or becomes clogged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fuel spilling out of the coolant system
fuel spilling onto exhaust components
engine stalling
loss of power
white smoke coming from the exhaust pipe
engine overheating
whining noise from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR cooler can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine overheating
smoke coming from the exhaust pipe
coolant leaking
EGR valve failure
engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high pressure oil pump can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
high pressure oil leak
engine overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
vehicle unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Failure to Restart
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of power steering and brakes, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. The failure to restart the engine can lead to further inconvenience and safety risks.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
the vehicle fails to restart
the check engine warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle coasts to the side of the road
the engine shuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the fuel rail is damaged
white smoke is visible
the engine overheats
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body and TPS can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the throttle body needs to be replaced
the TPS code is triggered
the vehicle has problems idling.
